# 4. まだ、辿り着けなくて

Shiho: That should be good for practice today. Nice work, everyone.
Saki: Yikes! No more! My fingers are cramping up...!
Ichika: Haha. To be fair, Saki, your part is pretty hard.
Shiho: Saki, make sure you ice your hands so that you don't get tendonitis.
Saki: Oh, yeah, I forgot! Thanks, Shiho!
Ichika: Right... It'd be awful to get injured just before our show.
Saki: But I still need more time to practice. My fingers really freeze up when I ice my hands.
Shiho: I understand how you feel, but resting is just as important, okay...?
Saki: O-Okay...!
Saki: (But... I'm still terrible. I really don't want to fall even further behind than I already am...)
Saki: (Wait, that's right...! I have a way to help everybody out...!)
Saki: So about coming up with our own song...
Ichika: Oh, sorry... I wasn't able to come up with anything new.
Honami: Me neither... I thought about it afterward when I got home, but drew a complete blank...
Shiho: I could only come up with one, and even then, it's just copying this band I listen to...
Ichika: How about you, Saki? Did you manage to come up with something?
Saki: Heh heh heh...
Saki: Ta-daa! Look! I've got a bunch here!
Honami: What...?! You mean all of these, Saki...?!
Shiho: One, two, three... You made ten?
Saki: Hehe. I got so many good ideas last night, and I wrote them all down!
Honami: That's incredible, Saki. There's so many...!
Ichika: You're right. All of these in one night...?
Saki: Hehe. Aren't I amazing♪
Shiho: Yeah, you are...
Shiho: I'd like to hear some of them. Mind playing one for us, Saki?
Saki: Sure! I'll play some right now!
Saki: And that's the last one. What do you think...?
Shiho: ...
Honami: I... I thought they all sounded really nice but...
Ichika: Exactly... They sounded modern like they were made to become popular...
Ichika: But...
Saki: But...?
Shiho: I can't put my finger on it...
Shiho: But I have a hard time imagining us playing any of these during an actual show.
Saki: Us during an actual show...
Honami: It's so strange too. These melodies are so well made too, and I wouldn't be surprised if I heard these played for a music show on TV...
Ichika: Yeah, they even sound cool but...
Saki: Nooo! Why is this so hard?!
Honami: I-I'm sorry, Saki! I know it's a little unfair for us to say anything like that since we didn't really contribute...
Shiho: Each phrase was put together really well and I could tell that a lot of thought went into them.
Saki: But if we can't agree on it as a band, they won't really be our songs... *Sob*
Shiho: Saki...
Shiho: There's no need for you to feel rushed. We agreed that it's going to take time for us to come up with our own songs, right?
Saki: Yeah, I know...
Ichika: But I understand how you feel, Saki.
Ichika: I want our song to be the best it can be too.
Honami: I agree with Ichika, and thank you for doing this for us, Saki...
Shiho: Then how about we use Saki's work as a basis next time to think about what kind of music we want to play as a band...?
Ichika: Okay. Let's sleep on it and see what we all come up with.
Saki: Yeah...! And I'll keep doing my best to come up with something that really hits home!
Saki: (It's a small step forward, but I'm helping everybody out...!)
Saki: (But...)
Saki: (I spent so much time on these yesterday...)
Shiho: ...
Saki: Hmm... What should I do...?
Saki: I focused on melodies yesterday, so I could try thinking about chords today...
Saki: Okay, let's do that! Maybe it'll sound more original then!
Saki: Alright, time to get to work!
Saki: Hmm...
Saki: I want to try making a few more, but I feel like I'm all over the place now...
Saki: This isn't working... What can I do to make it better?
Saki: I feel like I'm close, but none of them still sound right...
Saki: I really thought that I'd be able to help everyone by doing this too...
Shiho: It might be because we don't know exactly what kind of music we want to play yet.
Ichika: The kind of music we want to play...
Saki: ...
Saki: Come to think about it, what kind of music do I want to play...?
Saki: We decided to go pro together...
Saki: But I don't think I ever thought about what exactly I wanted to try playing.
Saki: *Sigh*
Saki: It's like nothing's going the right way now...
